From: Daniel Nylander <daniel@danielnylander.se>
Subject: [PATCH] GRIM: Add sscanf return check in sprite loading

Multiple sscanf calls in the Grim engine parse sprite file headers
without validating the return value. Corrupted sprite files cause
uninitialized variables to be used for dimensions and offsets,
potentially causing out-of-bounds memory access during rendering.

---
 engines/grim/sprite.cpp | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

Note: Similar pattern exists in engines/twp/font.cpp where sscanf
parses font metrics without return value checks.
